This paper deals with coded caching in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm for content placement, which is a topic that falls under distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also uses differential equations and concentration analysis to analyze the performance of the proposed scheme, which are techniques commonly used in statistical inference (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
